x = 1 + \frac{1}{2}\sin x
$$

考虑

$$
\begin{align*}
f(x) = x - 1 - \frac{1}{2}\sin x \\
\Rightarrow f&#039;(x) = 1 - \frac{1}{2}\cos x \geq 0
\end{align*}
$$

$f(x)$单调递增

$$f(1) = - \frac{1}{2} \sin 1 &lt; 0$$

$$f(\frac{\pi}{2}) = \frac{\pi}{2} - \frac{3}{2} &gt; 0$$

故只有唯一的零点$x_0 \in (1, \frac{\pi}{2})$

$$|Q&#039;(x_0)|= |\frac{1}{2}\cos x_0| &lt; 1$$

div.data-content:
$$
x = 1 + \frac{1}{2}\sin x
$$

考虑

$$
\begin{align*}
f(x) = x - 1 - \frac{1}{2}\sin x \\
\Rightarrow f'(x) = 1 - \frac{1}{2}\cos x \geq 0
\end{align*}
$$

$f(x)$单调递增

$$f(1) = - \frac{1}{2} \sin 1 < 0$$

$$f(\frac{\pi}{2}) = \frac{\pi}{2} - \frac{3}{2} > 0$$

故只有唯一的零点$x_0 \in (1, \frac{\pi}{2})$

$$|Q'(x_0)|= |\frac{1}{2}\cos x_0| < 1$$

故不动点为双曲吸引点
